"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-kimberley-woods-kayak-bronze-medal-paris-2024-b2587360.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  The Briton was distraught after finishing last in the kayak single final in Tokyo three years ago, .\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 216, \"end\": 226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Briton\", \"score\": 0.9999999999308784, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Briton\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q25379\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Briton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Briton\"}, {\"begin\": 292, \"end\": 297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.993314368749067, \"rank\": 0.006730626656854149, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Kimberley Woods'Olympic bronze medal-winning redemptiontook less than 150 seconds to confirm, but the wait felt like an eternity for the Rugby kayaker.\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 448, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Walsh\", \"score\": 0.8318640603567028, \"rank\": 0.2020781438112283, \"text\": \"Kimberley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 28-year-old, who three summers ago in Tokyo was visibly distraught after incurring 56 seconds worth of penalties for a bottom finish in her maiden Olympic final, was sitting in third position with just one competitor left who could knock her off the Paris podium - defending champion Ricarda Funk, the fastest finisher from the afternoon's semis.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 643, \"end\": 648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.993314368749067, \"rank\": 0.006730626656854149, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 855, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999992446647, \"rank\": 7.555110404302406e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ricarda_Funk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ricarda Funk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ricarda_Funk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ricarda_Funk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the German made a mistake at the bottom of the course a 50-second penalty to finish 11th in 149.08, ensuring Woods' 98.94 was good enough for her first Olympic medal behind first-placed Australian Jessica Fox and Poland's Klaudia Zwolinska, who snuck into silver with the penultimate run.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 961, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9984934569015992, \"rank\": 0.0013931241154972022, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1143, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9994785036467301, \"rank\": 0.0003814121225424987, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Fox_(actress)\", \"score\": 0.548202986974713, \"rank\": 0.8241415192508661, \"text\": \"Jessica Fox\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Fox_(actress)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Fox_(actress)\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_men's_national_volleyball_team\", \"score\": 0.7912768952934301, \"rank\": 0.25519830024620693, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_men's_national_volleyball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_men's_national_volleyball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Woods said: \\\"It feels absolutely incredible.\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not believe how long my journey's been.\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have been paddling for 20 years now and finally have a medal around my neck.\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ricarda Funk coming down, I could not watch.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was on my knees, I was head in hands not being able to watch and all of a sudden I heard the crowd shout something and there was a mistake and I was like, 'oh my god, I can not believe I have done it.'\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1667, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That whole journey of where I have come from in the last 10 years has been incredible.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am really proud of who I am today, being able to be open and speak, use my platform for good.\\\"\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Woods has been candid about her long-term struggles with mental health and self-harm, and twice checking into private mental health hospital the Priory and admitting to experiencing suicidal thoughts at her lowest points.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In an interview with theGuardian, the paddler, who was introduced to the sport by her aunt Diane - a silver medallist at the 1994 World Junior Championships - Woods revealed she had not harmed herself since after a race just before the TokyoOlympics.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2169, \"end\": 2174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diane_Chambers\", \"score\": 0.9999998161161043, \"rank\": 1.66675844056447e-07, \"text\": \"Diane\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diane_Chambers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diane_Chambers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With her first Olympic medal glittering around her neck, Woods reflected that, compared to her most challenging times, managing the darkest points of her internal battles, the bronze medal moment \\\"makes everything worth it.\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The journey I have been on, that first moment of admitting that I do need help, that's where I go back to.\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's okay to do that, it's okay to seek out help with the people that are close to me.\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have always been trying to be open with my coach of where I am at because I see him more than anyone else in my family.\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am still getting help today, topping up the toolbox and making sure I still have the skills to deal with whatever the Games has but also whatever life has.\\\"\", \"from\": 2875, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Woods bounced back in the years following her Tokyo heartbreak, claiming a bronze medal at the World Championships later in 2021, 10 days after she was involved in a car crash.\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3082, \"end\": 3087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.993314368749067, \"rank\": 0.006730626656854149, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In September, she claimed her first world title in kayak cross on home turf at the ICF Canoe Slalom World Championships in Lee Valley, where she also took C1 silver alongside gold and bronze in the C1 and K1 team events.\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3265, \"end\": 3270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"score\": 0.9999978655164384, \"rank\": 2.1344860886661304e-06, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\"}, {\"begin\": 3337, \"end\": 3347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Valley_White_Water_Centre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7816355390693378e-20, \"text\": \"Lee Valley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Valley_White_Water_Centre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Valley_White_Water_Centre\"}, {\"begin\": 3369, \"end\": 3371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9999999680121624, \"rank\": 3.1987997258555024e-08, \"text\": \"C1\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\"}, {\"begin\": 3412, \"end\": 3414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9999999680121624, \"rank\": 3.1987997258555024e-08, \"text\": \"C1\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Canoe_Slalom_World_Cup\"}, {\"begin\": 3419, \"end\": 3421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K-1\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 1.3375778819994301e-12, \"text\": \"K1\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K-1\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K-1\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Friday she will have a second crack at gold, this time in the event in which she is world champion, with kayak cross making its Olympic debut atParis 2024.\", \"from\": 3436, \"to\": 3594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3544, \"end\": 3549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"score\": 0.9999978655164384, \"rank\": 2.1344860886661304e-06, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For now, though slalom superfan Woods, who cannot wait to watch her team-mates in competition, said: \\\"I am kind of glad that I have got four days off just to chill out.\", \"from\": 3596, \"to\": 3764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am used to the (atmosphere) now.\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 3799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am probably maybe one of the favourites in the kayak cross but I am not thinking about that, I am just thinking about being out there and enjoying the crowd, and I can not wait to sit on top of that ramp.\\\"\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 4009, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4011, \"to\": 4241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4062, \"end\": 4073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8801005675900787e-15, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"